<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="116" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,356,521]" pageId="3" pageNumber="116">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,243,427,449]" pageId="3" pageNumber="116">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. Garcia, Ayala-Vasquez &amp; de la Fuente" authorityYear="2021" box="[267,447,428,450]" class="Pezizomycetes" family="Tuberaceae" genus="Tuber" kingdom="Chromista" order="Pezizales" pageId="3" pageNumber="116" phylum="Foraminifera" rank="species" species="mixtecorum">Tuber mixtecorum</taxonomicName>
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="116">
is characterized from other species in the 
<taxonomicName box="[867,976,428,449]" class="Pezizomycetes" family="Tuberaceae" genus="Tuber" kingdom="Chromista" order="Pezizales" pageId="3" pageNumber="116" phylum="Foraminifera" rank="species" species="maculatum">Maculatum</taxonomicName>
clade by the whitish to brownish grey peridium, composed of interwoven or postrate cells, with erect claviform terminal elements of 19–24 µm, ellipsoid ascospores of 15–33.9 × 11.3–23.3 µm and the putative association to
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[627,797,500,521]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="3" pageNumber="116" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="castanea">Quercus castanea</taxonomicName>
